01:39.148 --> 01:43.819
<i>Chiert, help me, suki, bliadi.</i>

01:44.945 --> 01:46.571
What are you looking for?

01:46.656 --> 01:48.573
[whispering] My mirror.
Where is my mirror?

01:48.658 --> 01:49.700
It's not there?

01:49.784 --> 01:52.577
Not unless it's suddenly turned invisible.

01:52.662 --> 01:54.622
I've been robbed.

01:56.957 --> 02:00.502
-Where is my mirror?
-What?

02:00.585 --> 02:02.963
The magnifying mirror.
The one from my desk.

02:03.047 --> 02:05.424
The one I've seen you use
for your eyebrows.

02:05.507 --> 02:06.759
I don't know.

02:07.927 --> 02:10.262
No one sleeps
when my things go missing.

02:10.345 --> 02:13.683
I'm not sleeping.
I can't sleep.

02:16.143 --> 02:18.729
Wake up.
My mirror is missing.

02:18.813 --> 02:21.023
We have to live together.
It would be pretty dumb to steal from you.

02:21.106 --> 02:22.942
Like you're all geniuses.

02:23.943 --> 02:25.610
-[snoring]
-Wake up, motorboat.

02:25.695 --> 02:27.571
Please, I didn't go to sleep
until you left for the shower.

02:27.655 --> 02:28.989
I swear,
I kept myself up.

02:29.073 --> 02:31.366
-Where is my mirror?
-On the desk?

02:31.450 --> 02:34.244
She wouldn't steal from you.
She's terrified of you.

02:35.913 --> 02:38.457
Why would I want to look
at myself in the mirror?

02:39.333 --> 02:42.127
Hey, Reznikov.
It's time to make the donuts.

02:42.211 --> 02:44.839
I'm not ready.
And my mirror is missing.

02:44.922 --> 02:47.091
I don't give a tiger's testicle.

02:47.174 --> 02:48.633
Look, the faster I deliver you,

02:48.718 --> 02:50.594
the faster I can get back
to my mindfulness practice.

02:50.677 --> 02:51.971
So, let's go!

02:52.054 --> 02:53.973
Do you think your time
is more valuable than mine?

02:54.056 --> 02:55.640
Fine. Fine.

02:55.725 --> 02:57.935
I'll put my face on in the kitchen, huh?

02:58.018 --> 02:59.561
[inmate] Shut up! I'm still asleep!

03:00.855 --> 03:02.022
Wait.

03:03.148 --> 03:04.649
Where's my lip pencil?

03:04.734 --> 03:06.276
[whimpers]

03:06.360 --> 03:08.863
Where the hell is my lip pencil?

03:08.946 --> 03:10.405
Now, Reznikov.

03:11.406 --> 03:15.660
Fucking thieves.
I will find you!

03:15.745 --> 03:17.913
[inmate] Shut the fuck up.

03:19.123 --> 03:21.500
Oh, shoot.
She left the light on.

03:28.799 --> 03:29.967
Thank you.

03:34.930 --> 03:36.348
[sobs]

03:36.431 --> 03:37.725
You okay?

03:39.643 --> 03:41.353
Not even a little bit.

03:58.620 --> 04:00.414
[inmates talking indistinctly]

04:05.002 --> 04:07.379
I'm not even looking.
I don't care.

04:08.588 --> 04:10.340
You're not even that hot.

04:11.383 --> 04:13.593
-Wait, maybe you are.
-[Judy whistles]

04:18.140 --> 04:22.227
[Judy] Now this is starting
to feel like overkill.

04:22.311 --> 04:23.395
-You think so?
-[Judy] Mmm.

04:23.478 --> 04:25.230
More like looks could kill.

04:25.314 --> 04:27.607
Check out the stink eye in this place.

04:27.691 --> 04:30.485
You know, maybe that's 'cause
there's a boy in the girls' room.

04:31.736 --> 04:34.073
These ladies don't seem
too bothered by me.

04:37.201 --> 04:38.202
[Judy groans]

04:38.285 --> 04:39.703
The bathroom is where
you're the most vulnerable.

04:39.787 --> 04:42.164
<i>-[scoffs]
-I mean, haven't you ever seen Psycho?</i>

04:42.247 --> 04:43.623
Or read an actuarial table?

04:43.707 --> 04:45.209
Yoga Jones ordered this protection.

04:45.292 --> 04:47.837
Frankly, I think it was
an overreaction. [chuckles]

04:47.920 --> 04:50.089
<i>[singing] ♪ I've been stealing
Them other ladies' pies ♪</i>

04:50.172 --> 04:52.424
<i>♪ And, ooh, that was a bust ♪</i>

04:52.507 --> 04:54.844
<i>♪ 'Cause them other ladies
Been fakin' when they bakin' ♪</i>

04:54.927 --> 04:56.636
<i>♪ Using that store-bought crust ♪</i>

04:56.720 --> 05:01.809
<i>♪ But Judy's pies is oh-so-tasty
And I never get my fill ♪</i>

05:01.892 --> 05:02.893
<i>♪ So blame it on... ♪</i>

05:02.977 --> 05:04.436
On the other hand...

05:04.519 --> 05:07.064
[Suzanne continues singing]

05:09.942 --> 05:12.027
I'll be, uh, right outside.

05:12.111 --> 05:15.072
<i>Oh, hey, you got the new O?
I was reading a good article.</i>

05:15.155 --> 05:18.033
Oh, you know,
I think McCullough walked off with that.

05:18.117 --> 05:19.659
Oh, here.

05:20.660 --> 05:22.329
<i>You want Women's Health?</i>

05:22.412 --> 05:24.289
-Thank you.
-Enjoy.

05:25.916 --> 05:29.044
Well, I believe those are my eggs.

05:29.128 --> 05:32.089
I only took one bite.
It was getting cold.

05:34.466 --> 05:35.717
[sighs]

05:39.972 --> 05:41.681
You know,
this is getting ridiculous.

05:41.765 --> 05:43.017
I can't spend the rest of my time

05:43.100 --> 05:44.977
with some ding-dong like that
following me around.

05:45.060 --> 05:47.646
Isolation perpetuates the rumors.

05:47.729 --> 05:49.481
That you hate black people?

05:49.564 --> 05:53.735
Look, it was the '80s, all right?
Everybody was a moron in the '80s.

05:53.818 --> 05:55.487
I just want to be able to walk around here

05:55.570 --> 05:58.949
without everybody looking at me
like I'm some kind of terrified bigot.

05:59.033 --> 06:01.660
Out there is overrated.

06:01.743 --> 06:04.663
[inhales sharply]
Why don't we have a TV brought in?

06:04.746 --> 06:06.540
Oh, no.

06:06.623 --> 06:09.209
You know, I wouldn't wanna risk

06:09.293 --> 06:14.173
sullying your karma, your chi
or whatever with such a base object.

06:14.256 --> 06:16.800
Idiot box. I believe
that's what you called it last week.

06:16.883 --> 06:18.760
Did I?
I don't remember.

06:18.843 --> 06:22.681
Mmm-hmm. And I think you called me
the idiot on the idiot box.

06:22.764 --> 06:24.058
Right?

06:24.141 --> 06:26.643
Well, it's starting
to look like it's true.

06:26.726 --> 06:29.646
And there... there's gotta be
some way to clear the air.

06:29.729 --> 06:31.648
Make reparations.

06:31.731 --> 06:34.193
Forty acres and some eggs.

06:34.276 --> 06:35.902
Why don't you tell them again

06:35.986 --> 06:40.115
how many black friends
you have in your kitchen and your field?

06:40.199 --> 06:43.327
Okay, you shut up,
you PC hippie hypocrite.

06:43.410 --> 06:46.705
I would wager that your last address
before you came here

06:46.788 --> 06:48.790
wasn't exactly in the inner city.

06:48.873 --> 06:53.963
At least I didn't talk to puppets
that used the word "jigaboo."

06:56.798 --> 06:58.675
[Judy] Hmm?

06:58.758 --> 07:00.427
No more eggs for you.

07:05.682 --> 07:08.102
[inmates talking indistinctly]

07:26.620 --> 07:28.413
<i>[woman] An inmate
from Litchfield Federal Prison</i>

07:28.497 --> 07:30.332
<i>is attempting to contact you.</i>

07:31.583 --> 07:33.752
-Cal!
-Piper!

07:33.835 --> 07:37.922
Cal! Cal, you have no idea
how badly I've wanted...

07:38.007 --> 07:39.258
to hear your voice.

07:39.341 --> 07:41.551
Well, would you rather
hear my voice?

07:41.635 --> 07:46.515
Or a pre-war Gibson banjo
that Earl Scruggs played at the Opry?

07:46.598 --> 07:48.183
<i>-Your voice, for sure.
-You're right.</i>

07:48.267 --> 07:51.020
You're right. I haven't earned it yet.
I need to practice more.

07:51.103 --> 07:54.939
So, you got Neri's message,
didn't you?

07:55.024 --> 07:56.191
What?
What message?

07:56.275 --> 07:58.818
Neri sent you a psychic message
to call us.

07:58.902 --> 08:02.197
[stammering] I was skeptical at first,
but, I mean, here you are.

08:02.281 --> 08:04.074
Cal, I've missed you so much.

08:04.158 --> 08:07.911
There's really nobody in here
for me to... talk to right now.

08:07.995 --> 08:09.371
We are pregnant!

08:11.456 --> 08:13.083
You got pregnant in the basement?

08:14.418 --> 08:17.212
[squeals] I mean, we...
we think that it might have

08:17.296 --> 08:21.425
actually happened in the laundry room
or maybe in the dining room.

08:21.508 --> 08:23.468
Um, we're not sure.

08:23.552 --> 08:27.347
Mom has a standing hair appointment,
Tuesdays from 11:00 to 1:00.

08:27.431 --> 08:30.350
And yet, her hair has never changed.
It's a mystery.

08:30.434 --> 08:32.394
I mean, we're not technically
supposed to tell anyone yet,

08:32.477 --> 08:35.438
because it's only eight weeks,
but I don't care, fuck it.

08:35.522 --> 08:36.940
Holy shit.

08:38.982 --> 08:42.196
Wow!
Congratulations.

08:42.279 --> 08:43.822
That's wonderful.

08:43.905 --> 08:46.158
It is pretty cool.

08:46.241 --> 08:48.243
I'm already bonding with the baby.

08:48.327 --> 08:52.747
I talk to him and I sing to him.
In English and in Korean.

08:52.831 --> 08:54.833
<i>Did I tell you
that we're all learning Korean?</i>

08:54.916 --> 08:56.793
<i>Oh, we've got
a whole new business, Pipes.</i>

08:56.876 --> 09:00.339
We ship used clothes over to Korea.

09:00.422 --> 09:02.924
<i>Vintage. Uh, podo suhwag.</i>

09:03.007 --> 09:04.884
I mean, we're killing it.
They can't get enough.

09:04.968 --> 09:08.347
Neri sweeps through
Goodwill, Sally Army, St. V's,

09:08.430 --> 09:11.683
and then she ships it over
to our friend, Helen Hong, in Seoul.

09:11.766 --> 09:14.018
I mean, ever since
the panties dried up,

09:14.103 --> 09:16.188
we were...
we were in real trouble,

09:16.271 --> 09:19.858
but babies bring luck and inspiration.

09:19.941 --> 09:21.401
<i>Yeong-gam.</i>

09:23.112 --> 09:25.864
What do you think
of the name "Clarence," huh?

09:25.947 --> 09:28.575
<i>-Clarence Chapman?
-Do you know it's a boy?</i>

09:28.658 --> 09:30.369
I don't.
Not yet.

09:30.452 --> 09:33.288
But I'm willing it to be a boy
because women are terrifying.

09:33.372 --> 09:35.374
<i>-Yeah.
-Yeah, yeah.</i>

09:35.457 --> 09:40.379
<i>Neri is pretty psyched
and I'm here to buy him his first banjo.</i>

09:40.462 --> 09:41.796
<i>-You can never start it too early.
-[sniffles]</i>

09:41.880 --> 09:44.841
<i>Music education sucks in schools now
which is, like, a total travesty...</i>

09:44.924 --> 09:47.136
-[voice breaking] Cal--
-No, I know. I... I know, I know.

09:47.219 --> 09:51.223
If it is a girl, and it could be,
she will play the fiddle.

09:52.141 --> 09:55.394
So, maybe... maybe I shouldn't
pull the trigger yet on the banjo.

09:58.730 --> 10:00.274
You're gonna be an amazing dad.

10:00.357 --> 10:02.859
I'm totally fucking scared
that I'm gonna fuck it all up.

10:02.942 --> 10:06.446
[sighs] I mean,
you know where we came from.

10:06.530 --> 10:08.948
You are so much warmer,
you are so much lovelier,

10:09.032 --> 10:10.909
and you are so much awesomer.

10:13.412 --> 10:15.872
Plus, you married the anti-Mom.
There's no way.

10:15.955 --> 10:17.499
<i>Stop it.</i>

10:17.582 --> 10:19.834
Wow.
That is so nice of you to say.

10:20.919 --> 10:22.546
I'm really glad you called, Pipes.

10:25.257 --> 10:29.136
I just wanted to check in,
and, um, hear your voice.

10:29.219 --> 10:31.763
<i>[man speaking on PA]
All Whispers employees report to the yard.</i>

10:31.846 --> 10:33.890
<i>Whispers employees to the yard.</i>

10:34.974 --> 10:37.852
Cal, I, uh... I gotta go.

10:38.812 --> 10:40.063
I love you, Daddy.

10:40.147 --> 10:44.193
Okay, yeah, love you.
Bye, Aunty Piper.

10:45.152 --> 10:47.529
-Okay, bye.
-Bye.

10:51.658 --> 10:53.160
[sobs]

10:55.787 --> 10:57.164
[sniffling]

11:01.000 --> 11:03.295
[breath trembling]

11:05.380 --> 11:07.632
[man speaking indistinctly on PA]

11:14.514 --> 11:17.058
Looks like you got light bugs.

11:17.141 --> 11:20.479
-Might be an infestation.
-Oh, gee. [chuckles]

11:20.562 --> 11:22.897
I don't know
what to do about that.

11:22.981 --> 11:26.276
You got any advice for me,
Miss Nichols?

11:26.360 --> 11:28.278
Darkness, Miss Morello.

11:29.238 --> 11:32.241
You fight the light with darkness.

11:32.324 --> 11:33.992
Care to visit me on the dark side?

11:34.075 --> 11:38.204
Well, actually, it's Mrs. Muccio now.

11:38.288 --> 11:40.374
